result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan W Ells was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

[MK] case called at 10:13am. 
Defendant Ryan W Ells in court with Attorney AnnMarie M. Sylla.  DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count # 2.

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Ells on Probation for one year, with conditions:
--to follow through with recommended treatment after undergoing an AODA assessment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling as may be required by the Agent
--to submit to random drug and/or alcohol screening
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to take all prescription medications as prescribed
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes or as deemed appropriate by the Agent 
--to obtain/maintain part-time or fulltime employment and/or education program as supervised by the Agent
--to submit a DNA 
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge as calculated by the clerk [amount listed by the clerk on the payment slip: $443].  This amount is to be paid through the Clerk of Courts Office. The Court grants Mr. Ells sixty days to pay this amount or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office.  Non-payment will result in 20 days in Jail with Huber privileges, consecutive.

Days credit for time already served: 0 days
The Court orders a Drivers License Suspension for a six month period. 
The Court finds that Mr. Ells is eligible for expungement of this case if Mr. Ells successfully completes the Probation term. 
recess 10:19am
